Web Sudo, when enabled, provides an added layer of protection against malicious attackers. However, for a legitimate user, it can be annoying, especially when the user is often using space admin functions.

The damage a compromised space admin account can cause is fairly limited, as they can't make changes at a site level.

Therefore, the Web Sudo feature would be improved by making it configurable at a space level. If activated, it would always need to protect the site level admin functions, but individual space admins should be able to choose whether or not it is needed for each space.

